"title": "6243: adultery, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6243",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In Scripture there is a close link between sexual sin and spiritual corruption and immorality as promoted by false teachers. Scripture frequently uses the language of sexual sin to expose the infidelity of God's people.</p>\n<h2>The link between sexual sin and spiritual adultery</h2>\n<h3>In practice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:1-Num25:3\">NUM 25:1–25:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:15\">EXO 34:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:14\">HOS 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>In false teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20-Rev2:25\">REV 2:20–2:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:15-Num31:16\">NUM 31:15–31:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:6\">2TI 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:13-2Pet2:15\">2PE 2:13–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:4\">JUD 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:8\">JUD 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:14-Rev2:16\">REV 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual adultery and God's covenant relationship with his people</h2>\n<h3>God as a husband to his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a></strong> <em>The spiritual relationship between God and his people is defined in terms of the intimate and exclusive bond of marriage.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5\">ISA 54:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:14\">JER 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31-Eph5:32\">EPH 5:31–5:32</a></p>\n<h3>God is jealous for his people's affections</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:14\">EXO 34:14</a></strong> <em>Just as husband and wife are jealous for their relationship in love, so God is jealous for the affections of his people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:4-Exod20:5\">EXO 20:4–20:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:23-Deut4:24\">DEU 4:23–4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13-Deut6:15\">DEU 6:13–6:15</a></p>\n<h2>The history of spiritual adultery among God's people</h2>\n<h3>Before Israel's kings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:16\">DEU 31:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:7-Lev17:9\">LEV 17:7–17:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:4-Lev20:6\">LEV 20:4–20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:16-Judg2:17\">JDG 2:16–2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:27\">JDG 8:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:33-Judg8:34\">JDG 8:33–8:34</a></p>\n<h3>In the northern kingdom of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:2\">HOS 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:25\">1CH 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:1-Ezek23:8\">EZK 23:1–23:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:2-Hos2:3\">HOS 2:2–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:10-Hos4:12\">HOS 4:10–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:3-Hos5:4\">HOS 5:3–5:4</a></p>\n<h3>In the southern kingdom of Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:1-Jer3:3\">JER 3:1–3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:10-2Chr21:11\">2CH 21:10–21:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:3-Isa57:8\">ISA 57:3–57:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:20\">JER 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:7-Jer5:8\">JER 5:7–5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:13-Jer23:14\">JER 23:13–23:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:15-Ezek16:22\">EZK 16:15–16:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:11-Ezek23:21\">EZK 23:11–23:21</a></p>\n<h3>In Jesus Christ's generation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:38-Matt12:39\">MAT 12:38–12:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:4\">MAT 16:4</a></p>\n<h2>God's judgment on spiritual adultery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:3-Jer19:5\">JER 19:3–19:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:6-Jer3:10\">JER 3:6–3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:10-Jer16:13\">JER 16:10–16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:36-Ezek23:49\">EZK 23:36–23:49</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are not to be drawn into spiritual adultery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:15-1John2:17\">1JN 2:15–2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:6-1Cor10:11\">1CO 10:6–10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:12-Heb3:14\">HEB 3:12–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:26-Heb10:31\">HEB 10:26–10:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4-Jas4:5\">JAS 4:4–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:21\">1JN 5:21</a></p>",
